headline.main: BROOKLYN CITY.; MY STERIOUS AFFAIR. MAYOR'S ANNUAL STATEMENT COURT CALENDAR.

docs.lead_paragraph: MYSTERIOUS AFFAIR.--Yesterday morning two Germans, named WILLIAM DUNKIRK and WEIDMISTER, pocketbook manufacturers, residing in Ross-street, near Wilson-street, East Brooklyn, were found in their bed, the former dead and the latter in a senseless state, from which it was impossible to remove him during the day, and it is supposed that the cannot recover.
